org.openimaj.audio

Class AudioAnnotator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.ml.annotation.AbstractAnnotator<OBJECT,ANNOTATION>
      • org.openimaj.ml.annotation.IncrementalAnnotator<DoubleFV,String>
        • org.openimaj.audio.AudioAnnotator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Classifier<String,DoubleFV>, FeatureExtractor<DoubleFV,SampleChunk>, Annotator<DoubleFV,String>, IncrementalTrainer<Annotated<DoubleFV,String>>

    public abstract class AudioAnnotator
extends IncrementalAnnotator<DoubleFV,String>
implements FeatureExtractor<DoubleFV,SampleChunk>
    A classifier/annotator for audio frames. Note that this is a pretty general annotator that takes DoubleFVs and String labels. The DoubleFVs can be extracted from audio with this class also, as it also implements FeatureExtractor interface for SampleChunks (returning DoubleFVs). However, there is no implementation for the necessary FeatureExtractor.extractFeature(Object) method, so subclasses must implement this. The default annotator in use is a general KNNAnnotator for DoubleFVs, however, this can be changed using setAnnotator(AudioAnnotatorType).
    Author:
    David Dupplaw (dpd@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
